<br>
More powerful/needed spells then mod rods...<br>
<br>
Clarity...Much of the game is based around it...It is REQUIRED for mana regen...Raids simply would not be possible without it.<br>
<br>
Slow....75% reduction in the mobs totale dmg...Unless the mob is Immune to speed changes this spell IS the most powerful spell in the game.<br>
<br>
Haste...Again Needed on raids the DPS would simply not be enough without haste to even kill a low lvl end game mob.<br>
<br>
Complete heal (you mentioned)<br>
<br>
tash/Malo...Mages can do a 35 one however the shammy one is almost always used...Debuffs are an essential part of raid sucess.<br>
<br>
Aego/hp buffs....A small series of spells many people over look again it does not have the &quot;flash&quot; of mod rods but without such buffs CHeal chains would become much elss effective Increasing the difficulty of encounters immensly.<br>
<br>
The problem yanbun is that you over look the &quot;little&quot; or &quot;common&quot; or old spells simply because they have been in the game for so long...The game is CENTERED around these spells they are essential for ANY raid.....Mod rod Builds off these spells...Lose any 2 of the above spells and you will not have a good raid.<br>
<br>
In luclin mages were repaired not suped up...Focus items were needed a long time ago to end the stagnation of casters in general now our DPS will scale with the zone/loot lvl of the zone...IE A bracer from VT will give +1-26% while a dmg 3 will only do 1-20% <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ...In PoP oober focus items might give 10-22% giving them a higher average dmg.<br>
