 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=wezloc>WEZLOC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 856<br> <font color=#333333>(9/29/02 7:58:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=68>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   hmmm</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> They are the best form of mana regen in the game. Better than Arch Lich, better than KEI, better than Bard song. We can control the rate at which mana flows into the game. And it holds no bounds.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
First of all Rod of Mystical Transvergence is not a mana regen spell. It is a mana transfer spell with a major drawback. Is the spell powerful? Yes. Is it as powerful as you are making it out to be? Heck No. What makes KEI and spells like it so great is that it regens mana over time. The spells are totally different and shouldn't be compared to one another. Reason being ask a cleric what class they want to group with if they had to pick? A enchanter with KEI or a Mage with Mod Rods...I am willing to bet 9 out of 10 will say Enchanter. <br>
<br>
Also Mod Rod &gt; Bard Song?  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Let me tell you if I had a choice between Mod Rods or a 13mana per tick, 15health regen per tick that was manaless and I could give it to anyone in a 150ft radius I would be all over it.<br>
<br>
T-Rods are nice to have but not needed in a group setting. They are a nice extra help while soloing but no where near on par with kei, bard song, or lich. On Luclin encounters they rock. Understand what I said...Luclin encounters. Velious encounters do not require mass rods, neither does Kunark encounters. Only the ssra temple and above encounters require T-Rods so IMO that hardly makes this spell second most powerful in the game when it is only needed for 5% of all the content in the game.<br>
<br>
