 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubalanzsonofanz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 1954<br> <font color=#333333>(9/30/02 12:30:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=77>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Responses, Immlazen, Wezloc, others...</span><hr size=1> Before I begin, a little semantics.  Expansions are probably best evaluated as <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  &quot;eras,&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and not evaluated solely based on what was released, which is uniformly buggy, unbalanced, incomplete, and singularly awful.<br>
<br>
Thus we live now in the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  &quot;Luclin Era,&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and it is proper to ask what mages got during this era.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Biggerin:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  And I don't see how raz is a &quot;verant poster boy.&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I can and will turn on <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> like a rapid weasel in a heartbeat when I think they have screwed up.  For example, if chaining pets is effectively <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>forced</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> on 61+ mages, that is a major foul up.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Imlazzen:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->   Other classes get this as a regular heal instead of having to put AA's into it...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->You want to be a pet cleric?  Try playing a beastlord then, they're better at it.<br>
<br>
As a magician, one of our main strengths is good cheap strong pets.  And that's what we got.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Immlazen:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  My RL brother (60 Wizard) even talks about how Magicians got screwed on there class AAs.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Someone who plays one of two classes with the best AA thinks mine stinks.  So what?  I have 80 AA and counting, and I don't regret a single one.  Rather than list them, here is my <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=154800">Magelo: Razamatazz Pizzazz</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Immlazen:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Trods, you play the mana battery. If I solo, where is my healer? Or do you have a alternate that you hunt with so you dont have to worry about healing back up?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->1) Read <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showMessage?topicID=18.topic">Transvergence and The Complete Magician</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
2) You don't need a healer, though it helps immensely<br>
3) What's an alt?  When I solo, I solo.<br>
<br>
I'm not going to repeat the basis for all my calculations here, but they are all in the thread referenced above.  For a mage with T-Rods, 3 HP ~= 1 Mana.  With any 50+ phantasmal armor spell, standing regen for a Mage with no AA is ~12 HP/tick.  By clicking a charge on a rod whenever hitpoints approach full, this is equivalent to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Flowing Thought 4</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Add <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Improved Regeneneration 3</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and this rises to FT5.  Hey!  I can summon a FT5 stick when I am all alone with no healer.<br>
<br>
When I hand a rod to another caster, since they did not pay the cost of the rod, for them, it is 4 HP ~= 3 Mana.  Give them a standing HP regen of 12 HP/tick is equivalent to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Flowing Thought 9</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Want some candy, little girl?<br>
<br>
Even better though, suppose you can't wait, but want the mana <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>now</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->.  You can click a charge, and assuming that you are not already terribly wounded, get the equivalent of over a minute and half's worth of medding instantly.  You can borrow mana from from the future at the cost of hitpoints.  What a deal.<br>
<br>
And this is solo.<br>
<br>
Throw in a cleric, a sweet class for a mage to partner with.  A typical mage-cleric duo using the Complete Heal/Rod cycle can generate 100 net mana per tick, including the cost of healing all the damage taken by clicking rods.  Oh, and that cleric is pretty good at keeping your pet alive, if that is critical for you.  During a raid, a shaman with <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Torpor</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> can keep you eating a rod every tick without adverse effect on your health.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Nerodread:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Pet fixes, not upgrades. <br>
<br>
It was about time too, pets were still Kunark-era.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Matter of opinion.  Mine was, when various mage balance remedies were being bandied about, that mage pets were in fact likely already strong enough, but the real problem was the large number of situations which prohibited their use.  So I recommend neutral faction pets, which was eventually implemented, much to most everyone's surprise, including mine.  I levelled to 60 and got a big chunk of AA well before the upgrades were made to the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Greater Vocarates</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and I did just fine.  Having the additional DPS is nice, and it certainly is an <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>upgrade</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> by definition.  Making pets neutral faction was a fix.  Raising the pet haste cap was fix.  Increasing the hitpoints and max damage of 55+ pets was an upgrade.  Likewise, the epic was upgraded.  Has anyone else's epic been comparably upgraded?<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Mystique Darkholme:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  We could very well end up with a zone that is full of elementals that aren't tagged as summoned and our mez/charm/fear/dispell won't work on them.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Almost certainly.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Immlazen:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  You try and nitpic at every little sentence I make.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->We are attempting to refute your claims.  I disagree strongly with both your conclusion and the logic behind them.  Quoting you makes it perfectly clear what point or line or reasoning I am arguing against.  Nothing personal, I do it to everyone.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Immlazen:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Matter of fact I was pointing out that a decent &quot;Heal&quot; spell would be better then chaincasting...Epic pet or no epic pet.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Well if you were talking about an essentially manaless heal, or one with an absurdly good ratio, then yes.  Make a good enough heal, and that would better than chaining.  Otherwise, why aren't the existing heals good enough for you?  How good is good enough?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>That</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> is likely to be a very interesting question, but I can tell you this.  It is very unlikely mages are going to get a heal anywhere approaching as good as beastlords.  They are, after all, based at least in part on a priest class, and one important tactic for them is <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  &quot;pet clericking.&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->   In contrast, our naked unbuffed pets are so good and so cheap, it's going to hard to come up with a heal that is both competitive with chaining and not absurdly good.<br>
<br>
Now if the PoP environment does indeed force chaining in the majority of encounters, then that is a bad thing, and a stronger pet heal is obvious possible remedy.  But as things stand now, it seems that the pet heals we have already, with <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>both</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> 50+ pet heals being <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Luclin</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> release spells, are adequate.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Wezloc:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  First of all Rod of Mystical Transvergence is not a mana regen spell.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Read above.  A summoned rod for a solo mage represents the equivalent of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Flowing Thought 4</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  5</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and in excess of FT100 in groups with a healer.  At the uber end, with <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Shield of Auras</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, a summoned rod is about FT85 with no healer.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Wezloc:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  It is a mana transfer spell with a major drawback.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->It is in addition a mana transfer spell with a drawback that nearly every group is equipped to deal with, i.e. replacing hitpoints, to the extent the drawback is nearly trivial.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Wezloc:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Is it as powerful as you are making it out to be? Heck No.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Heck yeah.  Look at <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Noonie</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->'s parses, for example, for the profound impact rods make on mage and group DPS.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  &quot;One rod to rule them all, one rod to bind them, one rod to bring them all, and in the darkness bind them!&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
RODPLZTHXKK?<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Wezloc:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Mod Rod &gt; Bard Song?  Let me tell you if I had a choice between Mod Rods or a 13mana per tick, 15health regen per tick that was manaless and I could give it to anyone in a 150ft radius I would be all over it.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Cleric01 one tells raid, 'Getting low on mana, rods please!<br>
Enchanter01 tells raid, 'Rod plz!'<br>
