<br>
Now you click it, gain 220 mana. Still a net loss.<br>
<br>
Ok you presummoned it, so mana not an issue.<br>
<br>
However when that 1st rod is gone.<br>
<br>
You make a rod.<br>
<br>
400 mana down.<br>
<br>
Click it twice. net gain of mana.<br>
<br>
Net loss of 600 hit points.<br>
<br>
1 charge left.<br>
<br>
Approach full health, click it. mod Rod all gone.<br>
<br>
Now resummon it for 400 mana, and your 220 mana of added mana is gone. Negated in resummoning a rod UNLESS you sit and med it up.<br>
<br>
That is why some want an improved mana regen spell.<br>
<br>
Self rodding only helps IF you have a cleric/healer.<br>
<br>
If solo, you get instant mana now, but med for it later. The next gain on any mod rod is 260 mana. Throw in spec for conjuration (AND HOPE you don't fizzle on a rod. I know I do at times), and the bet gain maybe 300 mana.<br>
<br>
300 mana is nice, it is HARVEST with side effects.<br>
